args: That day, the angels and apostles all set out\non an important mission.

Hearken to my voice. This village has been
occupied by a neighboring country, and our
mission is to free it and rescue the captive
priests and believers.
You will charge in from all four sides\nof the village. Rescue the hostages\nand annihilate any enemies you find.
We will inform you when it is time to\nmove. Please stand by until then. Over.
I have briefed the apostles on our plan and\nwill leave the commands to you, Regina.
Oh, sorry. Good work relaying that info.

...Okay, you know what's bugging me?
We JUST finished cleaning up the Satan
mess, and now we have to deal with
invaders. There's not even time to breathe.

I believe that is by the enemy's design.
Grams suffered massive losses with
Satan's revival, making this the best
opportunity for them to make a move.
I know. And just as they hoped, we let\nthem waltz on in and take this village\nwithin our borders.
But regardless, their tyranny ends now;\nI've got a trick up my sleeve for this\nparticular mission.
By Her name, we'll show them that the\nterritory of Grams remains protected by\nIlia's grace!
Everyone has arrived at their\ndesignated positions.
Good. Let the angels and apostles know\nthe operation is starting.
Nevin and Ramiel have encountered\nhostiles. Requesting orders.
Initiate combat. If they can hold out for a\nbit, Pinon and Gabriel will meet them and\ncatch the enemy in a pincer maneuver.
Understood. I will convey the information.
Nevin and Pinon have met up.\nThey carried out their pincer attack\nand defeated the enemies.
(Regina's strategies truly are amazing.\nShe knows exactly what is happening on\nthe battlefield even from this distance.)
Hmm? Oh, sorry. Uh, just tell\nPinon and Nevin to stand by.
(They're standing by at a time like this?\nThis feels overly confident, but I am\ncertain Regina has something planned.)
(This is odd. Regina hasn't given Nevin's\ngroup any new orders since having them\nstand by.)
(Even if this is part of her plan, they've\nbeen inactive for far too long. Perhaps\nI should ask her what she intends to—)
Understood! I'll tell Regina at once\nand request further orders.
Ryszarda and Raphael are surrounded and\nstruggling to fight off the enemy.
Wait, that shouldn't be happening.\nWhat is Nevin's group doing?
They are on standby, and have been for\nsome time now.
What the hell?! I told them to stand by\nuntil they saw an opening to meet up\nwith Ryszarda again!
No... I swore I gave those orders...\nDid I only DREAM I gave them?
I'm so sorry! This is all my fault!
No. Apologies can wait. Right now,\nwe need to get Ryszarda out of this.\nTell them to deploy our secret weapon!
Understood. ...Ryszarda. Raphael.\nYou have permission to use our\nsecret weapon.

This is a paralyzing smokescreen I made
using chemicals created from alchemy.
It'll stop the enemy in their tracks and
let us regain our footing again.
Afterward, Regina's orders became more focused.\nWe continued the operation without any additional\nmishaps and freed the village.
I'm so, so sorry. I can't apologize enough.
Might I ask for an explanation, Regina?\nIt is not like you to forget an order,\nand I would like to know the reason.
Overwork, most likely. I stayed up for days\ntrying to develop that smokescreen, and it\nmust have hit me harder than I thought.
I knew we'd be in trouble if they used\nthe hostages as human shields.

I thought we needed something nonlethal
that could immobilize the enemies while
we rescued the hostages, so I was in a big
rush to make it.
But I overworked myself and wound up\nmessing up my orders. I took my eye off\nthe ball, and it cost us.
I need to really think about how this all\nwent down. And when everyone gets back,\nI'll apologize to all of them as well.
Anyway, I'm going to go. Please just\nlet me sleep, all right?
I suppose I have no choice but to admit\nthat Ramiel's warning was accurate.
I was so convinced Regina was a second\nMetatron that I may have overestimated\nher abilities.
No matter how much research she was\ndoing, it would never have affected \nMetatron's ability to think.
I see the limits of a human now.\nIt truly is a shame...
